Cloud Serive Support Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)

Version 1.0

Effective Date: 5/16/2023

1. Purpose:
   Procedure for supporting services on AWS or any cloud service

2. Responsibilities:
   Monitor Cloud based services
   Maintain and backup (snapshots or equivalent)
   
3. Definitions and Abbreviations:
   Cloud: Services based on the internet
   Backup: Copying files and data to a different location (usually one on a different drive/ on the cloud)
   Data: Files and settings
   
4. Procedure:
   Review any spicework tickets for any potential issues
   In case there is a problem define the solution as clear as possible and make a plan on how to deal with said problem to minimize any downtime 
   schedule a downtime and give as specific details regarding time as possible
   Make sure that before any changes are made the service is stopped
   Peform plan to deal with issue
   If taking longer than expected make sure to notify users of expected time of when the service is available
   Remember to start the service again after issues are resolved
   
5. Safety Considerations:
   Ensure the cloud services are down when performing tasks such as maintenace or backups
   Notify users of expected downtimes

6. Troubleshooting and Problem Solving:
   Make sure to refer to cloud service providers maintainence schedules 

7. References:

8. Revision History:
